definitions.definition: The great circle midway between the celestial poles; the celestial equator.
Of or relating to the spring or autumnal equinox.
definitions.example: an equinoctial gale or storm, i.e. one happening at or near the time of the equinox, in any part of the world

definitions.definition: Of or relating to the celestial equator.
Equatorial: Of or relating to the equator of the Earth.
